  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180°C/ 160°C (fan)/ gas 4</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Deseed the<strong> yellow pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Crush 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> <strong>garlic cloves </strong>open by squashing with the side of a knife and remove the skins</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1649176273394-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1649176273394-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1649176273394-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1649176273394-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1649176273394-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>dried oregano </strong>and a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1649176281985-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1649176281985-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1649176281985-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1649176281985-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1649176281985-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped yellow pepper</strong>, <strong>crushed garlic</strong> and <strong>spelt</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Pour over the <strong>tomato stock</strong>, add a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong> and cover with <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for an initial 30 min – this is your <strong>tomatoey spelt tray bake</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1649176290679-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1649176290679-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1649176290679-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1649176290679-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1649176290679-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>remaining garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Grind the <strong>chopped basil </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> to form a paste</p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and mix well – this is your <strong>basil oil</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don't have a pestle and mortar, chop everything very finely and mix with the oil</p>",
